3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The use of a Gauss-Markov source and the Kalman-Bucy filter are both techniques commonly used in machine learning, which could make this paper relevant to the machine learning community. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The term "intersymbol interference" suggests a possible application in digital signal processing, which is a subfield of multimedia. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with communication channels, which could be relevant to networking and internet architecture.
